CHANGES0250: Rewrite Omniscience.agda to use NFinCofin Bridge instead of NormalForms

Summary:
- Removed dependency on NormalForms.agda (normalFormExists-trunc no longer imported)
- Added imports for Bridge, NFC.Definitions, and Pres (NFinCofin.Presentation)
- Defined char2-B∞ and char2-B∞×B∞ inline (trivial from Boolean ring structure)

New private helper section (replaces old f-kernel-from-trunc infrastructure):
- FC module alias, FC≡ (Σ≡Prop for ℕfinCofinBA)
- φ-seq: extracts the characteristic sequence ℕ → Bool from φ_FC(x)
- φ_FC-injective: injectivity of φ_FC via roundtrip
- gen-absorb→bit-true: g∞(n)·x = g∞(n) ⟹ φ-seq(x)(n) = true
- αn-true→gen-absorb: φ-seq(x)(n) = true ⟹ g∞(n)·x = g∞(n)

f-kernel rewritten:
- Uses φ_FC-injective + all-bits-false (by case split on α(n))
- Each true bit leads to g∞(n)·x = g∞(n), hence f(g∞(n)) = 0, contradicting g∞-nonzero
- Much simpler than the old normalFormExists-trunc + joinForm/meetNegForm approach

f-no-retraction rewritten:
- Uses isFiniteOrCofinite classification (non-truncated prop) directly
- Fixed: α₁-odd-true and α₂-even-true now use gen-absorb→bit-true (previously had buggy inline copies)
- Fixed: arithmetic proofs for N ≤ suc(2·N) and N ≤ 2·N (previously wrong)
- Three cases: both-cofinite (product contradiction), Fin α₁ (bounded vs infinite), Fin α₂ (bounded vs infinite)

Compilation status: submitted for verification, pending result.
